# Cloud Run Configuration Persistence Migration

The current architecture saves your configuration (AI API keys, Job Source toggles, etc.) to a local JSON file (`/tmp/data/ai-config.json`). Because Google Cloud Run completely destroys its temporary file system every time it scales down or deploys new code, your settings are constantly being wiped out.

To make everything you write or toggle in the UI stay permanently, we need to bypass the ephemeral file system and save this data directly into your Supabase database.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. New Supabase Storage Table
We will create a universal key-value store table in your Supabase database to hold all app configuration and AI usage logs.

### 2. Refactor `storage/index.ts`
We will rewrite the core storage engine (`src/lib/storage/index.ts`) so that `readObject`, `writeObject`, `readCollection`, and `writeCollection` communicate directly with Supabase via `createServiceClient()` instead of using the local file system.

### [MODIFY] `src/lib/storage/index.ts`
- Integrate Supabase database client.
- Map file paths to the new `storage_kv` table.
- Implement silent fallback to the file system if Supabase is unreachable.

## User Action Required
Because your Supabase instance is hosted remotely on the cloud, I cannot run database migrations directly from my terminal. 

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To proceed, you will need to open the **Supabase Dashboard** -> **SQL Editor** and run a simple SQL script that I will provide. This script will create the `storage_kv` table.

## Job Source API Keys Reference
You asked for the variables needed for the job sources. Even with UI persistence, it is a best practice to set API keys as Cloud Run Environment Variables. Here are the keys you need to add to your Cloud Run service settings:
- `ADZUNA_APP_ID`
- `ADZUNA_APP_KEY`
- `REED_API_KEY`
- `THEMUSE_API_KEY`
- `JOOBLE_API_KEY`
- `FINDWORK_API_KEY`
- `GEMINI_API_KEY`

If you approve this plan, I will provide the exact SQL script for you to run in Supabase, and then I will rewrite the storage code.
